    "# Notebook 13 — Reading and Interpreting Phylogenetic Trees\n",
    "\n",
    "**Module:** 08 — Bioinformatics: Sequence Analysis  \n",
    "**Notebook:** 13 of 18  \n",
    "**Time estimate:** 60 minutes\n",
    "\n",
    "> Being handed a tree and asked to interpret it is a common interview and paper-reading\n",
    "> scenario. This notebook is pure biology + visual literacy."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 1 — Motivation\n",
    "\n",
    "A phylogenetic tree is meaningless until you can read it. What does it mean for two\n",
    "taxa to share a node? What is a clade? How do branch lengths encode time or rate?\n",
    "When is a tree rooted vs. unrooted? These questions appear in every evolutionary\n",
    "biology paper and many bioinformatics interviews."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 2 — Intuition\n",
    "\n",
    "A phylogenetic tree is a hypothesis about evolutionary history. Each **internal node**\n",
    "is a hypothetical common ancestor. Each **branch** represents an evolutionary lineage.\n",
    "**Branch length** encodes either time (a timetree) or number of substitutions per site\n",
    "(a molecular tree).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key rule:** you can rotate any internal node (swap left/right children) without\n",
    "changing the tree's biological meaning. Only the branching pattern matters, not the\n",
    "visual left-right arrangement."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 3 — Biological Background\n",
    "\n",
    "**Vocabulary:**\n",
    "- **Leaf (tip/taxon):** an observed sequence or species\n",
    "- **Internal node:** a hypothetical ancestor\n",
    "- **Root:** the most ancient ancestor (deepest node). Only rooted trees have this.\n",
    "- **Clade (monophyletic group):** a set of taxa comprising a common ancestor and all\n",
    "  its descendants\n",
    "- **Outgroup:** a taxon known to be outside the group of interest, used for rooting\n",
    "- **Branch length:** in molecular trees, number of substitutions per site\n",
    "- **Bootstrap support:** % of bootstrap replicates recovering this clade\n",
    "- **Sister group:** the clade most closely related to a given clade\n",
    "\n",
    "**Common misreadings:**\n",
    "1. \"A is more evolved than B\" — trees don't imply directionality of evolution\n",
    "2. \"A is ancestral to B\" — taxa at tips are contemporaneous (usually); only internal\n",
    "   nodes represent ancestors\n",
    "3. \"A and B are closely related\" without checking — you must look at the topology,\n",
    "   not the visual proximity on the page"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Step 6 — Python Implementation: tree visualization\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.patches as mpatches\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def plot_primate_tree():\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Draw the canonical primate phylogeny as a rectangular cladogram.\n",
    "    Annotates key concepts.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 8))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # --- Panel A: Rectangular cladogram with annotations ---\n",
    "    ax = axes[0]\n",
    "    ax.set_xlim(-0.1, 5)\n",
    "    ax.set_ylim(-0.5, 6)\n",
    "    ax.axis('off')\n",
    "    ax.set_title('Annotated Primate Phylogeny\\n(rectangular format)', fontsize=11)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Leaf positions (y-axis)\n",
    "    leaves = {\n",
    "        'Human':    (4, 5),\n",
    "        'Chimp':    (4, 4),\n",
    "        'Gorilla':  (4, 3),\n",
    "        'Orang':    (4, 2),\n",
    "        'Gibbon':   (4, 1),\n",
    "        'Mouse':    (4, 0),  # outgroup\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Internal nodes (x = depth from root)\n",
    "    internals = {\n",
    "        'HC_anc':    (3, 4.5),  # Human-Chimp ancestor\n",
    "        'HCG_anc':   (2, 4.0),  # +Gorilla\n",
    "        'ape_anc':   (1.5, 3.0), # +Orang\n",
    "        'hominoid':  (1.0, 2.0), # +Gibbon\n",
    "        'root':      (0.5, 1.0), # root (primate)\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "    colors = {'Human': '#2196F3', 'Chimp': '#4CAF50', 'Gorilla': '#FF9800',\n",
    "              'Orang': '#9C27B0', 'Gibbon': '#F44336', 'Mouse': '#795548'}\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Draw branches (horizontal then vertical)\n",
    "    branch_specs = [\n",
    "        # (from_x, from_y, to_x, to_y)\n",
    "        (3, 4.5, 4, 5),   # HC_anc -> Human\n",
    "        (3, 4.5, 4, 4),   # HC_anc -> Chimp\n",
    "        (2, 4.0, 3, 4.5), # HCG_anc -> HC_anc\n",
    "        (2, 4.0, 4, 3),   # HCG_anc -> Gorilla\n",
    "        (1.5, 3.0, 2, 4.0), # ape_anc -> HCG_anc\n",
    "        (1.5, 3.0, 4, 2), # ape_anc -> Orang\n",
    "        (1.0, 2.0, 1.5, 3.0), # hominoid -> ape_anc\n",
    "        (1.0, 2.0, 4, 1), # hominoid -> Gibbon\n",
    "        (0.5, 1.0, 1.0, 2.0), # root -> hominoid\n",
    "        (0.5, 1.0, 4, 0), # root -> Mouse\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "\n",
    "    for x1, y1, x2, y2 in branch_specs:\n",
    "        # Horizontal then vertical\n",
    "        ax.plot([x1, x2], [y1, y1], 'k-', lw=1.5)\n",
    "        ax.plot([x2, x2], [y1, y2], 'k-', lw=1.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Draw leaves\n",
    "    for name, (x, y) in leaves.items():\n",
    "        ax.plot(x, y, 'o', color=colors[name], ms=10)\n",
    "        ax.text(x + 0.05, y, name, va='center', fontsize=10,\n",
    "                color=colors[name], fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Draw internal nodes\n",
    "    for name, (x, y) in internals.items():\n",
    "        ax.plot(x, y, 'ks', ms=7)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Annotations\n",
    "    ax.annotate('Clade: Great Apes\\n(monophyletic)', xy=(1.5, 3.0), xytext=(0.1, 4.5),\n",
    "                arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', color='blue'), color='blue', fontsize=8,\n",
    "                fontweight='bold')\n",
    "    ax.annotate('Sister group\\nto all others', xy=(4, 0), xytext=(2, -0.3),\n",
    "                arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', color='brown'), color='brown', fontsize=8)\n",
    "    ax.annotate('Bootstrap 98\\n(very confident)', xy=(3, 4.5), xytext=(3, 5.5),\n",
    "                arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', color='green'), color='green', fontsize=8)\n",
    "    ax.text(0.5, 5.8, 'Root (outgroup placed here)', fontsize=8, color='gray', ha='left')\n",
    "    ax.text(0.5, -0.3, 'Outgroup (Mouse)', fontsize=8, color='#795548')\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('← Past                              Present →')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # --- Panel B: Common misreadings ---\n",
    "    ax2 = axes[1]\n",
    "    ax2.axis('off')\n",
    "    ax2.set_title('Common misreadings to avoid', fontsize=11)\n",
    "\n",
    "    misconceptions = [\n",
    "        (\"Misconception 1:\", \"'A is more evolved than B'\",\n",
    "         \"Truth: Tips represent present-day taxa. The tree\\ndoesn't rank taxa by 'advancement'.\"),\n",
    "        (\"Misconception 2:\", \"'Chimp is ancestral to Human'\",\n",
    "         \"Truth: Both are contemporaneous. The common ancestor\\nis the internal node between them.\"),\n",
    "        (\"Misconception 3:\", \"Visual proximity = closeness\",\n",
    "         \"Truth: You can rotate any internal node. Only the\\ntopology (branching pattern) matters.\"),\n",
    "        (\"Misconception 4:\", \"Long branch = long time\",\n",
    "         \"Truth: Long branch = many substitutions. Time and rate\\nare confounded without a clock.\"),\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "\n",
    "    for i, (label, wrong, right) in enumerate(misconceptions):\n",
    "        y_pos = 0.95 - i * 0.25\n",
    "        ax2.text(0.05, y_pos, f\"{label} {wrong}\", transform=ax2.transAxes,\n",
    "                 fontsize=10, color='red', va='top', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "        ax2.text(0.05, y_pos - 0.05, right, transform=ax2.transAxes,\n",
    "                 fontsize=9, color='darkgreen', va='top')\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.savefig('phylogenetic_tree_interpretation.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "plot_primate_tree()"
   ]
  },
